# =============================================================================
# CORRECTED 2026-06-18 — Pix's real tracking policy (see CLAUDE.md §9A).
# Anything that is IP, a decision, or working material that informs a later
# decision is gitignored AT THE TIME IT IS CREATED and never enters the remote.
# The remote carries ONLY the runnable product; TimeMachine backs up the local
# material. (The earlier "full working store / keep DARCSI_OVERVIEW" framing was
# written in error by an agent — removed.)
# >> WHEN YOU CREATE such a file, add its path/pattern below in the SAME action.
# >> Never `git add -A` — stage explicitly.
# =============================================================================

# Project working memory, status & overview (decision-informing — local only)
/CLAUDE.md
/TASKS.md
/DARCSI_OVERVIEW.md

# Code prompts for Claude Code + session scaffolding (ephemeral working docs)
*-CODE-PROMPT.md
/benchvision-code-session-starter-*.md

# Design exports & design-prompt working docs
/design/
*-design-prompt.md
/design-system-design-prompt.md

# Working briefs / checklists / model notes (root — decision-informing)
/fleet-layer-model-brief.md
/devon-bench-pc-verification-checklist.md

# Kept on purpose — the RUNNABLE PRODUCT ONLY (do NOT add ignore rules for these):
